7:
Welcome home? This is a pub.
...Why are all the waitresses dressed 
like maids?
9:
Oh, this must be your first time 
visiting your "summer home." The 
Maids' Parlor is themed restaurant—
you can dine like a noble, for just a 
fraction of the cost!
11:
In addition to dining and catering, we 
also offer real housekeeping services 
and quest support! What can we do 
for you today, Milord?
14:
Uh... Um... How about just a table for 
two?
17:
Of course, Milord. What sort of maid 
would you like as your server? 
Tsundere? Cute and peppy? A little old 
lady with a twinkle in her eyes?
20:
Oh, gosh, um... H-how about someone
with a sweet smile?
24:
What are you, ten? You're bright red, 
Alk. 
...Look, just send someone who's not 
gonna be afraid of the big scary tiger-
man, and I'm good.
27:
I know the perfect maid, Milord! Tough 
as nails, with a sweet smile to boot. 
Marianne, come prepare the parlor, 
please!
34:
Marianne, reporting for duty. What are
your orders, Commander?
37:
Silly-willy, these are the "lords" of the 
manor, remember?
41:
Oh. *ahem*
Can I take your order, Milords?
44:
See, you're getting the hang of it! 
...Let's get them to a table before 
taking their orders though, okay? This 
way, please!
47:
She wasn't kiddin' about the "tough" 
part…
55:
Um, do you have any 
recommendations off the menu?
58:
Hold that thought, Milord.
Threat at eleven-o-clock. I'll handle it.
63: Let me take it from here. Stand back.
66:
Oooh! Now YOU'RE more my style! 
Gwehehahaha! Can I get a smile, 
sweetie?
68:
Hmph. I've got something better—
something that'll have you head over 
heels.
71:
Time to take out the trash. Have a 
nice TRIP!
75:
Threat eliminated. Returning to my 
patrol route. 
...Oh, and we hope to see you again 
soon.
80:
Man, you sent him FLYING! Heh, you're 
not bad!
83:
It was just a drunk, unarmed civilian. 
I've handled worse.
86:
Ehehe, Marianne is super strong—she 
can open even the toughest of pickle 
jars! Oh, also, if you still need help 
deciding what to get, Marianne makes 
a mean omelette!
88:
Really? I could go for an omelette. Do 
you need another minute Nimbus, or 
are you ready to order?
92: I'll go for the omelette too.
97:
Very well, Milord. I'll execute the orders 
straight away... w-with all my heart?
102:
Whew, I'm stuffed! That was really 
good!
106:
Yeah, the food was great, even if it did 
feel like we were bein' stared down the 
whole time.
109:
You didn't notice, Alk? Marianne's been
watching us. It's givin' me 
goosebumps…
114:
Apologies, Milord. I'm supposed to 
keep an eye on the floor in case 
anyone needs something. I didn't 
mean to stare you down.
117:
You were just keeping an eye on the 
floor? I thought I was next in line for 
the broom…
119:
But hey, who am I to talk. Old habits 
die hard, huh?
122:
That friend of yours'll soften you up 
eventually. Mine did.
126:
I know, but... I don't want to make 
extra work for her.
129:
Pardon me, Milord. Your time is 
almost up.
130:
If you'd like to keep chatting with 
Marianne, why not try our 
housekeeping services?
132:
She's really neat and organized, so 
she'll have your place shipshape in no 
time! And, and—!
134:
...She works harder than anyone I 
know. She's got discipline, poise, and— 
And she's a perfect maid! You'll see!
137:
Hm, what do you think, Nimbus? We 
COULD use a little help around 
Starview.
140:
She's basically like a mercenary that 
cleans, right? Sounds handy.
144:
I guess we'll give it a go then—if you're 
up for it, Marianne.
152:
I'm proficient in cleaning out enemy 
bases, mine-sweeping, pest 
extermination, and washing 
bloodstains. Just give the orders, sir.
156:
Heh. Sounds good to me. You have 
any experience with the Kaleidoscope?
159:
Plenty. I can lead a week-long 
operation—with zero casualties.
162:
Great! Man, I never knew maids were 
this helpful. I thought they just 
feather-dusted stuff.
165:
We do—usually. Oh, Marianne, DO 
clean something while you're over 
there, please. You're a maid, not a 
mercenary, remember?
170: I know, but... he's the one who asked...
